metadata.name: Levitation #194
metadata.description:
Abstract structures floating in space. 

——————

Levitation continues my exploration of Suprematism and Geometric Abstraction. It contains my developments and ideas for the past half a year.
Starting as mostly inspired by Kleine Welten (Small Worlds) series by Wassily Kandinsky, the collection evolved more into Suprematic compositions.

——————

To change the size of an image, open it in live view and add ‘&size=[size (6200 max.)]’ to the end of the URL.

Controls:
[Arrow Up / Down] — increase / decrease animation speed.
[R] — skip the animation.
[C] — switch between clean and grainy versions.
[S] — save the image.

Created using p5.js and GLSL.
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.

——————

hrunz. — Nov. 2022.

metadata.name: Vortex #208
metadata.description:
"Vortex" is a free collection (giveaway) mainly for holders of "Virtual Treasure" https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/21113
which had been added automatically in the whitelist and free for everyone :) 

KEYS:

- 1-4: Set resolution from 1x to 4x of the current dimension (possibly slower performance in higher values)
- S: Save a png file with the current resolution

----
Made with p5js, glsl

metadata.name: sin titulo #149
metadata.description:
S/T - Proyecto #8 // Untitled Project #8

Project released for fxhash anniversary week 11/14–18 - 2022


Keys:

[1,2,3] -> change pixel density. Or can be passed via url ?pd=5 produce 6000x9000pix. Be aware for the file size in render. 
[s] -> download canvas capture.
[double tap] -> download canvas capture on mobile
